# DeepSeek Provider Rules

Docs: https://api-docs.deepseek.com/  
Pricing: https://api-docs.deepseek.com/quick_start/pricing  
OpenAI-compat shapes: `examples/openai-openapi/` (local reference; do not vendor)

**Base URL (OpenAI format) default:** `https://api.deepseek.com` — see
`internal/config/urls.go`.  
(Anthropic-compat URL exists upstream; **MVP uses OpenAI chat completions only**.)

## Supported models (MVP)

| API model ID | Role |
| ---- | --- |
| `deepseek-v4-flash` | Default cheap / high-volume execution |
| `deepseek-v4-pro` | Harder reasoning / agentic execution |

**Deprecated aliases (upstream, do not prefer in our map):** `deepseek-chat`,
`deepseek-reasoner` (historically flash non-thinking / thinking; sunset
2026-07-24 UTC per DeepSeek docs). Prefer `deepseek-v4-flash` / `deepseek-v4-pro`.

## Thinking / sampling (MVP)

| Concern | Guidance |
| ---- | --- |
| Thinking | Prefer explicit `thinking: {"type":"enabled"\|"disabled"}` (+ optional `reasoning_effort`) per DeepSeek docs — **do not** apply Moonshot K2 `thinking` or K3-only `reasoning_effort` semantics blindly |
| Tools / JSON | Supported on v4 flash & pro — still run gateway sanitizer for Cursor quirks |
| Streaming | OpenAI-compatible SSE family; separate reasoning vs content when present |
| Auth | `Authorization: Bearer {DEEPSEEK_API_KEY}` only |

Official first call: https://api-docs.deepseek.com/

## Out of MVP (document only)

- Anthropic Messages base URL (`/anthropic`) — not the Cursor OpenAI override path
- FIM / chat-prefix beta endpoints unless a later task adds them

### `DeepSeek thinking param mismatch`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| 400 / unexpected thinking on v4 | Sent Moonshot-only params or omitted DeepSeek `thinking` object | Apply **provider-aware** sanitize from model map (`deepseek` row); see `gateway.mdc` |

### `Routed to DeepSeek without API key`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Upstream 401 after alias maps to DeepSeek | Only Moonshot key saved | Require `deepseekKeyEncrypted` when resolved provider is `deepseek` (doctor / set-key) |

